President Obama has nominated Michael McGowan to serve as the U.S. Marshal for the District of Delaware. McGowan has a strong background in public safety, having served as the New Castle County Director for United States Senator Christopher Coons since 2011. Prior to that, he spent 22 years with the New Castle County Police Department, retiring as the Chief of Police in 2011. McGowan is affiliated with the Police Executive Research Forum and serves on the Board of Directors for the Better Business Bureau of Delaware. He holds a Bachelor's degree from the University of Delaware and a Master's degree from Wilmington University. If confirmed, McGowan will be responsible for protecting the citizens of Delaware.